Territory of Washington, County of Spokane}ss Territory of Wash, Plaintiff vs. Ray Raymond Defendant}ss In the District Court of the Territory of Washington, and for the Fourth Judicial District thereof, holding terms at Cheney Spokane Falls, Spokane County, in said.
To the Sheriff of Spokane County Greeting: In the Name of the United States, You are hereby commanded to summon J.M. Morgan W.A. Webb S.H. Whitehouse to be and appear before the 4th Jud. Dist Court Wash Ter. at the Court House, in Cheney Spokane Falls in said County, on the 16th day of December A.D. 1886 at 9 o'clock A.M. to there give evidence in the above entitled cause on the part of said Defendant.
Witness the Hon. George Turner, Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of Washington Territory, and Judge of said Court, and the Seal thereof affixed this 2 day of Dec. A.D. 1886. D.A. Clement Clerk By Chad B. Johnston Deputy.
